    "These techniques may enable the generation of molecules designed to meet specific requirements, potentially overcoming the limits of current scoring systems (for instance, because of non-additivity, activity cliffs (Kwapien et al., 2022; Özçelik et al., 2022).",
    "A promising structure-based design may address de novo design for as-yet-undiscovered macromolecular targets (Volkov et al., 2022), by producing molecules that match specific binding sites' electrostatic and shape properties.",
    "Potential shortcomings and bias in available protein-ligand affinity databases may account for the lacklustre practical implementation of structure-based de novo design (Graff et al., 2021).",
    "There is untapped potential in fields like polypharmacology and selectivity that might benefit significantly from fine-grained control over various aspects of de novo designs.",
    "Exorbitant expense (of GAI setup) and biased GAI models are further obstacles."
